<div id="review_14328601" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/14328601" />
    <a title="Cleo Maranski" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/453205-cleo-maranski"><img alt="Cleo Maranski" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1600916834p2/453205.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/14328601?book_show_action=true">Feb 01, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cleo Maranski" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cleo Maranski" href="/user/show/453205-cleo-maranski">Cleo Maranski</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer14328601" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7375304816067233550">This book was such a disappointment. The characters were completely one dimensional and not at all interesting. The storyline was filled with cliches from every bad Lifetime movie. About three quarters of the way through, I somehow knew how it would end (because it was the one cliche that hadn&apos;t been hit yet). The book itself is primarily dialouge and not good one at that. Avoid.</span>
  <span id="freeText7375304816067233550" style="display:none">This book was such a disappointment. The characters were completely one dimensional and not at all interesting. The storyline was filled with cliches from every bad Lifetime movie. About three quarters of the way through, I somehow knew how it would end (because it was the one cliche that hadn't been hit yet). The book itself is primarily dialouge and not good one at that. Avoid.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7375304816067233550" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


