<div id="review_3837208704" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3837208704" />
    <a title="exploraDora" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/36234199-exploradora"><img alt="exploraDora" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1525708467p2/36234199.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3837208704?book_show_action=true">Mar 15, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="exploraDora" class="user" itemprop="url" name="exploraDora" href="/user/show/36234199-exploradora">exploraDora</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/51851163-firefly-lane">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/36234199-exploradora?shelf=audiobook">audiobook</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/36234199-exploradora?shelf=adult">adult</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3837208704" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8314762249065587107"><b>***4 stars***</b><br/><br/>DNFed this book at chapter 32/37 - not because it&apos;s not good, but because it got to a point where I wasn&apos;t comfortable reading on.<br/><br/>As I was halfway through, I spoiled myself by reading an article comparing the book to the TV show and I found out that <a class='jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction'>(view spoiler)</a><span class='spoilerContainer' style='display: none'>[Kate dies of cancer. That was when I decided I would stop reading once she was diagnosed.<br/>Anything after that would be too heartbreaking for me to read on, because I recently lost my dog to lung cancer at the age of only 8 </span></span>
  <span id="freeText8314762249065587107" style="display:none"><b>***4 stars***</b><br /><br />DNFed this book at chapter 32/37 - not because it's not good, but because it got to a point where I wasn't comfortable reading on.<br /><br />As I was halfway through, I spoiled myself by reading an article comparing the book to the TV show and I found out that <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[Kate dies of cancer. That was when I decided I would stop reading once she was diagnosed.<br />Anything after that would be too heartbreaking for me to read on, because I recently lost my dog to lung cancer at the age of only 8 years and ever since I get triggered by pretty much anything related to death by (unexpected/sudden) illnesses. <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span> <br /><br />But Firefly Lane is a beautiful novel about family, love and most of all about friendship. It follows the unlikely friendship of two very different teenage girls from the moment they first meet and into their adulthood, all the way to 30 years later when they're still bffs. It beautifully depicts the ups and downs of this relationship and how it changes through the years as they mature. <br /><br />If you like contemporary fiction about friendships and don't mind having your heart broken, I do recommend this one.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8314762249065587107" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


