<div id="review_3830687800" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3830687800" />
    <a title="DeAnn" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5299664-deann"><img alt="DeAnn" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1309203098p2/5299664.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3830687800?book_show_action=true">Mar 03, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="DeAnn" class="user" itemprop="url" name="DeAnn" href="/user/show/5299664-deann">DeAnn</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3830687800" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11266249429749569483">4.5 friendship stars (rounded up for all the tears)<br/><br/>This is a book all about friendship between two different girls who grow into women as the book progresses. There are lots of fun song references (both in the book and the Netflix series) that really help place you in the time periods, from the mid 1970s-through the 2000s. I loved how the story developed and somewhere I read that the girls were so different because of how they were raised. Kate has the traditional family with both parents and a </span>
  <span id="freeText11266249429749569483" style="display:none">4.5 friendship stars (rounded up for all the tears)<br /><br />This is a book all about friendship between two different girls who grow into women as the book progresses. There are lots of fun song references (both in the book and the Netflix series) that really help place you in the time periods, from the mid 1970s-through the 2000s. I loved how the story developed and somewhere I read that the girls were so different because of how they were raised. Kate has the traditional family with both parents and a brother at home and Tully has had a tumultuous childhood, partially raised by her grandmother and partially raised by a freewheeling mother hooked on drugs and alcohol. She seeks her mother's approval and love, but is most often disappointed. At school, Tully is cool and Kate is nerdy! The two end up living next door near Seattle and ultimately become best friends.<br /><br />Tully is focused and ambitious, determined to make her way in journalism and broadcasting and she wants Kate to be right by her side. Tully is beautiful and attracts men like crazy as she makes her way up in the world. Kate does love to write but not sure she wants to be in the same competitive industry. Their friendship has some ups and downs with Tully's forceful personality and ambition. Kate ends up married and with a family and it made for interesting dynamics between the two women. What is the better choice, career or a family? Or can you have both? The book is long enough that we get to know both women very well.<br /><br />When I got towards the end of this book, I could only read for about 10 minutes at a time as I stopped, found my box of Kleenex and collected myself! That tells you how much these characters grew on me! Now I can't wait to read book #2.<br /><br />(I was definitely intrigued by the Netflix series and I got to preview the first two episodes early and I was hooked! I finished the series and I ended up buying this Kindle book since the library hold list was GIANT long! The series does depart from the book, but I enjoyed both equally!)<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="11266249429749569483" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


